Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteExclusiveGroups(25.10)                      deleteExclusiveGroups(25.10)

Name
       deleteExclusiveGroups - Deletes existing exclusive regions for groups

Syntax
        deleteExclusiveGroups

       [-help]

       [-all | <group_name>]

       Deletes existing exclusive regions for groups. You can use this command
       after  creating  exclusive groups. It restores all attributes of exclu-
       sive groups

Parameters
       -all   Deletes all exclusive regions. When specified, the  tool  resets
              all  existing  exclusive groups attributes to their default val-
              ues.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       <group_name>
              Specifies the name of the group to delete. The tool deletes  ex-
              clusive  regions of the specified groups and all other exclusive
              groups that have been created together. You can specify  one  or
              multiple groups after the command.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each deleteExclusiveGroups parameter. For a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man deleteExclusiveGroups

Examples
              * The  following command deletes all exclusive regions of groups
                (A,B,C,D,E,F).

                deleteExclusiveGroups -all

              * The following command deletes exclusive regions  of  groups  A
                and F.

                deleteExclusiveGroups {A F}

              * The  following  command  deletes  exclusive  regions of groups
                (A,B,C).

                deleteExclusiveGroups B

Related Information
